<p><span class=3D"latex-for-amp">=E2=87=92=E2=88=A0O=E2=80=99DO</span> =3D =
<span class=3D"latex-for-amp">=E2=88=A0PBO</span>&nbsp;(<em>Corresponding A=
ngles</em>)</p>
<p>Thus, <span class=3D"latex-for-amp">=E2=88=86OO=E2=80=99D</span>~<span c=
lass=3D"latex-for-amp">=E2=88=86OPD&nbsp; </span>(By <em>AA criterion of si=
milarity</em>)</p>
<p>Hence, according to condition for similar triangles the ratio of corresp=
onding sides must be equal:</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}\Rightarrow \frac{h=E2=80=
=99}{h} =3D \frac{r=E2=80=99}{r} =E2=80=A6(2)\end{array} \)</div>
<p>Substituting this value in equation (1),</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}V =3D \frac{1}{3}~ \pi \lef=
t(r^2 \left(\frac{rh=E2=80=99}{r=E2=80=99}\right)~-~r=E2=80=99^2 h=E2=80=99=
\right)\end{array} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}\Rightarrow V =3D \frac{1}{=
3}~ \pi h=E2=80=99~ \left(\frac{r^3~-~r=E2=80=99^3}{r=E2=80=99}\right)=E2=
=80=A6(3) &nbsp; &nbsp;\end{array} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>As it can be seen from fig 3,</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}h =3D H~+~h'\end{array} \)<=
/div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Substituting this value in equation (2),</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}\frac{h=E2=80=99}{H~+~h=E2=
=80=99} =3D\frac{r=E2=80=99}{r}\end{array} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}\Rightarrow \frac{h=E2=80=
=99}{H} =3D \frac{r=E2=80=99}{r~-~r=E2=80=99}\end{array} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}h=E2=80=99 =3D H\left(\frac=
{r=E2=80=99}{r~-~r=E2=80=99}\right)\end{array} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Substituting this value of <span class=3D"latex-for-amp">h=E2=80=99</spa=
n> in equation (3), we get</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}V=3D\frac{1}{3}\pi H(\frac{=
r{=E2=80=98}}{r-r{=E2=80=98}})(\frac{r^3-r{=E2=80=98}^3}{r{=E2=80=98}})\end=
{array} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}V=3D\frac{1}{3}\pi H(\frac{=
r-r{=E2=80=98}}{r-r{=E2=80=98}})({r^2+rr{=E2=80=98}+r{=E2=80=98}^2})\end{ar=
ray} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}\Rightarrow V =3D \frac{1}{=
3}~ \pi H~(r^2~+~r=E2=80=99r~+~r=E2=80=99^2)\end{array} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>This gives the required volume of frustum of cone.</p>
<h2><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Surface Area of Frustum of Cone</span=
></h2>
<p>Similarly, the surface area will also be the difference of the surface a=
reas of both the cones.</p>
<p>Curved surface area of right circular cone 1 =3D <span class=3D"latex-fo=
r-amp">=CF=80rl</span></p>
<p>Curved surface area of right circular cone 2 =3D <span class=3D"latex-fo=
r-amp">=CF=80r=E2=80=99l=E2=80=99</span></p>
<p>Curved surface area of the frustum of cone =3D <span style=3D"font-weigh=
t: 400;">=CF=80</span><i><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">rl</span></i><sp=
an style=3D"font-weight: 400;"> =E2=80=93 =CF=80</span><i><span style=3D"fo=
nt-weight: 400;">r=E2=80=99l=E2=80=99</span></i></p>
<p>Also, from fig. 3 ,in the <span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">t</span><spa=
