<p><img loading=3D"lazy" class=3D"alignnone" src=3D"https://cdn1.byjus.com/=
wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Frustum-Of-A-Cone-4.png" alt=3D"Frustum of Cone =
4" width=3D"750" height=3D"512"></p>
<p>From fig. 3 as the <span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">=CE=94OO=E2=80=B2D =
~&nbsp; =CE=94OPB</span>&nbsp;therefore:</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}\Rightarrow \frac{l=E2=80=
=99}{l} =3D \frac{r=E2=80=99}{r}=E2=80=A6(4)\end{array} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Also from the figure given above: <span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">&nbs=
p;</span><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">l=E2=80=B2 =3D l =E2=88=92 L</sp=
an></p>
<p>Substituting this value of <span class=3D"latex-for-amp">l=E2=80=99</spa=
n> in equations (4),</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}\frac{l~-~L}{l} =3D \frac{r=
=E2=80=99}{r}\end{array} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}l=3DL~\left(\frac{r}{r~-~r=
=E2=80=99}\right)=E2=80=A6(5)\end{array} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The circumference of the base is the length of arc <span style=3D"font-w=
eight: 400;">&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">S and S=E2=80=
=99, </span>, which is given by:</p>
<p>S=E2=80=99=3D <span class=3D"latex-for-amp">2=CF=80r=E2=80=99</span></p>
<p><span class=3D"latex-for-amp">S</span>&nbsp;=3D <span class=3D"latex-for=
-amp">2=CF=80r</span></p>
<p>From the figure,</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}Curved\ surface\ area\ of\ =
frustum,\ A =3D \frac{1}{2}~(Sl~-~S=E2=80=99 l=E2=80=99)\end{array} \)</div=
>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}\Rightarrow A =3D \frac{1}{=
2}~\times ~2\pi rl~-~\frac{1}{2}~\times ~2\pi r=E2=80=99\left({lr=E2=80=99}=
{r}\right)\end{array} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}\Rightarrow A =3D \pi l~\le=
ft(r~-~\frac{r=E2=80=99^2}{r}\right)\end{array} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}\Rightarrow A =3D \pi l~\le=
ft(\frac{r^2~-~r=E2=80=99^2}{r}\right)\end{array} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>From equation (5), substituting the value of <span class=3D"latex-for-am=
p">=E2=80=9Cl=E2=80=9D</span>,</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}\Rightarrow A =3D \pi L \le=
ft(\frac{r}{r~-~r=E2=80=99}\right)\left(\frac{r^2~-~r=E2=80=99^2}{r}\right)=
\end{array} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}\Rightarrow A =3D \pi L~(r~=
+~r=E2=80=99)\end{array} \)</div>
<p>Thus, the curved surface area of the frustum of a cone is:</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}A =3D \pi L~(r~+~r=E2=80=99=
)\end{array} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Where,</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}L =3D \sqrt{H^2~+~(r~-~r=E2=
=80=99)^2}\end{array} \)</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The total surface area is given as the sum of curved surface area and th=
e area of the base. Thus the total surface area of the frustum is:</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"mathjax-scroll">\(\begin{array}{l}Total\ surface\ area\ of\ f=
rustum\ of\ cone\ =3D \pi L~(r~+~r=E2=80=99)~+~\pi r^2~+~\pi r=E2=80=99^2\e=
nd{array} \)</div>
<h2><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Solved Problem</span></h2>
<p>A cone is cut by a plane horizontally. The radius of circular top and ba=
se of frustum are 10m and 3m, respectively. The height of frustum is 24m. I=
f the height of the cone is 28m, then find the lateral surface area of frus=
tum.</p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Solution: Let,&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Radii are r<sub>1</sub><span style=3D"=
font-weight: 400;"> =3D 10m and r<sub>2</sub></span><span style=3D"font-wei=
ght: 400;"> =3D 3m</span></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Height, h =3D 24m</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">First we need to find the slant height=
 of frustum, by the formula:</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">l =3D =E2=88=9A[(r</span><span style=
=3D"font-weight: 400;"><sub>1</sub></span><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;"=
> =E2=80=93 r<sub>2</sub></span><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">)<sup>2</=
sup></span><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">&nbsp;+ h<sup>2</sup></span><s=
pan style=3D"font-weight: 400;">]</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">=3D =E2=88=9A{(10 =E2=80=93 3)</span><=
span style=3D"font-weight: 400;"><sup>2</sup></span><span style=3D"font-wei=
ght: 400;"> + 24<sup>2</sup></span><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">}</spa=
n></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">=3D =E2=88=9A(49 + 576)</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">=3D =E2=88=9A625 m&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">=3D 25 m</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Lateral surface of frustum =3D =CF=80(=
r</span><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;"><sub>1</sub></span><span style=3D=
"font-weight: 400;"> + r<sub>2</sub></span><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;=
">)l</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">LSA =3D =CF=80(10+3)25</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">=3D 325=CF=80 sq.m.</span></p>
